umentation\/SwiftGodot\/UndoRedo","type":"reference"},{"text":" objects associated with edited scenes. Each scene has its own undo history and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorUndoRedoManager","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" ensures that each action performed in the editor gets associated with a proper scene. For actions not related to scenes ("},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProjectSettings"},{"text":" edits, external resources, etc.), a separate global history is used.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The usage is mostly the same as ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/UndoRedo","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". You create and commit actions and the manager automatically decides under-the-hood what scenes it belongs to. The scene is deduced based on the first operation in an action, using the object from the operation. The rules are as follows:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the object is a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node"},{"type":"text","text":", use the currently edited scene;"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the object is a built-in resource, use the scene from its path;"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the object is external resource or anything else, use global history."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This guessing can sometimes yield false results, so you can provide a custom context object when creating an action.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorUndoRedoMana